description:
Japanese title: Shitō! Ichigo VS Ichigo, 死闘！一護VSイチゴ.

At a Soul Reaper supply shop, Rukia picks up a mod soul to take over Ichigo's body while he's pulling Soul Reaper duty.
name: Fight To The Death! Ichigo vs. Ichigo

description:
Japanese title: Nuigurumi kara Konnichiwa, ぬいぐるみからコンにちは.

Rukia and Ichigo track the mod soul in Ichigo's body to a local elementary school.
name: Greetings from a Stuffed Lion

description:
Japanese title: Roku Gatsu Jū-shichi Nichi, Ame no Kioku, 6月17日、雨の記憶.

On the anniversary of his mother's death, Ichigo intends to take the day off from Soul Reaper duties and visit her grave with the rest of his family.
name: June 17, A Memory of Rain

description:
Japanese title: Taosenai Teki, 倒せない敵.

Ichigo faces the Grand Fisher, a Hollow that uses a lure in the shape of a little girl...
name: Unbeatable Enemy

description:
Japanese title: Burari Reijō Totsugeki no Tabi!, ぶらり霊場突撃の旅！.

When television hero Don Kanonji schedules a live recording of his hit show "Spirit Hunter" at a local abandoned hospital, Ichigo is surprised to see that an actual demi-Hollow is being summoned for the show.
name: Assault On Trip At Sacred Ground!

description:
Japanese title: Densetsu no Kuinshī, 伝説のクインシー.

Ichigo is unaware that one of his classmates, Uryu Ishida, possesses spiritual power of his own.
name: The Legendary Quincy

description:
Japanese title: Yasashii Migiude, やさしい右腕.

In order to prove how useless Soul Reapers are, Uryu releases bait to draw Hollows to their town. Whoever gets rid of the most wins the challenge.
name: A Gentle Right Arm

description:
Japanese title: Hana to Horō, 花とホロウ.

Orihime is paid a visit by a Hollow at school and discovers her own spiritual powers...
name: Flower And Hollow

deck: Between holding down the church and going on a rescue mission, our group is spread pretty thin. Is this going to be the breaking point?
name: Crossed

description: Kanan and Ezra try to protect an Imperial deserter by distracting the Imperial forces but it results in a confrontation.
name: Gathering Forces

deck: Constantine deals with a boy who is possessed.
description: When a young boy is taken over by a malevolent spirit, John (Matt Ryan) must put aside his misgivings over exorcising a child and convince the parents that their boy is not all that he seems.
name: Rage of Caliban

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Terrifying Blue-Eyes White Dragon

Japanese: Senritsu no Burū Aizu Howaito Doragon (戦慄のブルーアイズ・ホワイト・ドラゴン)

Yugi and his friends are in awe over Grandpa’s collection of Duel Monsters cards, but when #1 ranked duelist and ruthless tycoon, Kaiba, kidnaps Grandpa to get the rare Blue-Eyes White Dragon card, Yugi must face Kaiba in the ultimate Duel Monsters showdown and avenge his Gramps!
name: The Heart of the Cards

character_credits.name: Winged Dragon, Guardian of the Fortress #1

first_appearance_characters.name: Winged Dragon, Guardian of the Fortress #1

deck: Rick's group attempts to rescue Beth and Carol.
name: Coda

description: “Barry is thrilled when Oliver, Felicity and Diggle come to Central City to investigate a case involving a deadly boomerang. Excited about teaming up with his friend, Barry asks Oliver if he’d like to help him stop Ray Bivolo (guest star Patrick Sabongui), the meta-human Barry is currently tracking. Bivolo causes people to lose control of their emotions and has been using that skill to rob banks. Unfortunately, the superhero partnership doesn’t go as smoothly as Barry expected. When Oliver tells Barry he still has a lot to learn, Barry sets out to prove him wrong by attempting to stop Bivolo alone. However, when Bivolo infects Barry and sets him on a rage rampage, everyone is in danger, and the only one who can stop him is the Arrow. Meanwhile, Iris is furious when Eddie tries to get a task force to stop The Flash, Joe and Dr. Wells agree the Arrow is a bad influence on Barry, and Caitlin and Cisco deal with a new team in S.T.A.R. Labs.”
name: Flash vs Arrow

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Trap of Illusionist No Face

Japanese: Iryūjonisuto Nō Feisu no Wana (幻想師ノー·フェイスの罠)

Yugi and friends take a break from honing their card playing skills to watch Weevil and Rex Raptor compete in the Duel Monsters Regional Championship. When Yugi opens a package from Duel Monsters creator, Maximillion Pegasus, Yugi is forced to face him in the mysterious Shadow Realm where all the monsters and magic are real. Yugi loses, and Pegasus claims Grandpa’s soul as his prize! Yugi must travel to the Duelist Kingdom and win Pegasus’s tournament if he is ever to see his Grandpa again!
name: The Gauntlet is Thrown

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Lost Exodia

Japanese: Ushinawareshi Ekuzodia (失われしエクゾディア)

Yugi gives up one of his own Star Chips so that Joey can board the boat bound for Duelist Kingdom and duel to save his sister’s eyesight while Téa and Tristan stowaway to join their friends. But when word spreads that Yugi was the one who defeated World Champion Kaiba, the cheat Weevil tires to cripple Yugi’s deck by tossing his best cards overboard just as they reach the island!

Note: Exodia was only seen in card form.
name: Journey to the Duelist Kingdom

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Insector Combo

Japanese: Insekutā Konbo (インセクターコンボ)

Once Yugi and his friends reach Duelist Kingdom, Pegasus announces that there are many strange secrets on the island which will make his ultimate tournament unlike any they’ve ever had. But when Weevil begins to use these mysterious new rules against Yugi in a duel, Yugi must not only figure the rules out, but master them if he’s to survive!
name: Into the Hornet's Nest

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Ultimate Perfect Form, Great Moth.

Japanese: Kyūkyoku Kanzentai Gurēto Mosu (究極完全態 グレート・モス)

After Yugi defeats Weevil’s first wave of Duel Monsters, he’s shocked to discover that Weevil has one last trick up his sleeve; a ravenous Great Moth that grows in power with every turn! Can Yugi find a way to destroy this winged beast before it destroys him?
name: The Ultimate Great Moth
The Light at the End of the Tunnel

description: Raven tries to put the spirit of Halloween back in Halloween.
name: Halloween

description: The Titans try to settle the eternal question: Are boys or girls better?
name: Boys vs. Girls

description: When Cyborg is sick, Robin insists on shrinking to cell size to fight Cyborg's infection himself.
name: Body Adventure

description: A road trip in Cyborg's T-Car is really fun - for a while.
name: Road Trip

description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.
name: Thanksgiving

description: When the other Titans are too lazy to fight Brother Blood, Robin calls on his secondary team: Team Robin, a crime-fighting group made up of different Robins.
name: The Best Robin

description: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful spectre.
name: Ghost Fly

description: Jake finds himself transported to a world both alien and familiar.
name: Everything's Jake

description: After a memorial for a fallen ally, Jake starts acting very strange.
name: Is That You?

description: Jake sets out to fulfill a bizarre lifelong ambition.
name: Jake The Brick

description: Finn's aching tooth leaves him with no other option but to GO DENTIST
name: Dentist

description: When the Fire Kingdom is struck by a natural disaster, Flame Princess turns to an unlikely ally.
name: The Cooler

description: In a distant age, the wizard Evergreen quests to save the world.
name: Evergreen

description: While in art class, Zed (Angelica Celaya) has a bizarre vision of snakes that lead her and John (Matt Ryan) to a small town where a preacher has mysteriously gained the ability to heal his congregation.
name: Blessed Are the Damned

description:
Japanese title: Senaka Awase no Shitō!, 背中合わせの死闘！.

In the midst of their battle, Ichigo finds out that Uryu is a Quincy, a group with a long-standing rivalry with Soul Reapers.
name: Back To Back, A Fight To The Death!

description:
Japanese title: Kon no Uhauha Daisakusen, コンのウハウハ大作戦.

Rukia worries that news of Ichigo's battle with Menos Grande will attract the attention of the Soul Society.
name: Kon's Great Plan

description:
Japanese title: Abarai Renji, Kenzan！,阿散井恋次、見参！.

Rukia, wandering the streets at night, runs into two Soul Reapers from the Soul Society, Renji Abarai and her brother, Byakuya Kuchiki...
name: Encounter, Renji Abarai!

description:
Japanese title: Ichigo, Shisu!, 一護、死す！.

Ichigo fights Renji Abarai, a lieutenant from the Soul Society. When it looks like Ichigo might win, Byakuya Kuchiki steps in and deals a fierce blow...
name: Ichigo Dies!

description:
Japanese title: Torimodose! Shinigami no Chikara!, 取り戻せ！死神の力！.

Summer vacation begins, but it's all work for Ichigo, who starts training with Urahara in order to enter the Soul Society and save Rukia.
name: Reclaim! The Power Of The Shinigami

deck: The Flash takes on the Reverse Flash.
description: Barry (Grant Gustin) finds himself face-to-face with his nemesis, the man in the yellow suit, a.k.a. Reverse Flash, who killed his mother. Barry is frustrated when the Reverse Flash escapes, but Dr. Wells (Tom Cavanagh) and Cisco (Carlos Valdes) come up with a plan to trap him. All they need is bait, so they turn to Dr. Tina McGee (guest star Amanda Pays) from Mercury Labs to help. Meanwhile, it's Christmas at The West household and Iris (Candice Patton) is in full holiday cheer. Eddie (Rick Cosnett) gives her a surprising gift but also leaves her with a question that could change her life. Joe (Jesse L. Martin) joins the search for the man in yellow and ends up in the crossfire. Caitlin (Danielle Panabaker) finds Ronnie (Robbie Amell).
name: The Man In the Yellow Suit

has_staff_review.name: The Flash: Episode #107 - "The Man in the Yellow Suit"

deck: The League of Assassins give Oliver 48 hours to find Sara's killer, or Starling City citizens will die. Oliver then has an epic confrontation with Ra's al Ghul.
description: RA’S AL GHUL GIVES OLIVER AN ULTIMATUM; DINAH LANCE PAYS LAUREL A VISIT — Nyssa (guest star Katrina Law) returns to Starling City and tells Oliver (Stephen Amell) that her father, Ra’s al Ghul (guest star Matt Nable) has given Oliver 48 hours to find Sara’s killer or the League of Assassins will start killing the citizens of Starling City. Laurel (Katie Cassidy) is stunned when her father (Paul Blackthorne) delivers a very special Christmas gift – her mother, Dinah (guest star Alex Kingston). Meanwhile, Ray (Brandon Routh) tries to make amends with Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) and Oliver sets a meeting with Ra’s al Ghul.
name: The Climb

description: A call from Anne Marie (guest-star Claire van der Boom), a member of the fateful Newcastle crew, sends John (Matt Ryan) and Chas (Charles Halford) to Mexico City and brings them closer to the source of The Rising Darkness. Meanwhile, Zed's (Angelica Celaya) past comes back to haunt her.
name: The Saint of Last Resorts

has_staff_review.name: Constantine Episode 108 - "The Saint of Last Resorts"

deck: Peggy is contacted by Howard Stark after he gets in a bit of trouble.
description: Peggy is contacted by old acquaintance Howard Stark when he is framed for unleashing his deadliest weapons and can trust no one else. To help Peggy clear Stark’s name, he insists his butler, Edwin Jarvis, be at her beck and call–whether she likes it or not. But the risk is great: If caught, Agent Carter could be targeted as a traitor and spend the rest of her days in prison…or worse.
name: Now is Not the End

has_staff_review.name: Agent Carter Episode 101 - " Now is Not the End"

deck: Agent Carter has to recover a stolen weapon designed by Howard Stark.
description: Howard Stark’s deadliest weapon has fallen into enemy hands, and only Agent Carter can recover it. But can she do so before her undercover mission is discovered by SSR Chief Dooley and Agent Thompson?
name: Bridge and Tunnel

description:
Japanese title: Ichigo, Horō ni Ochiru!, 一護、ホロウに墜ちる！.

In the Soul Society, Rukia learns that in 25 days, she'll be taken to the Central Execution Grounds to face her punishment.
name: Ichigo Becomes A Hollow!

description:
Japanese title: Ichimaru Gin no Kage, 市丸ギンの影.

Ichigo completes lesson three of Urahara's training and learns the name of his zanpaku-to.
name: Ichimaru The Silver Shadow

description:
Japanese title: Totsunyū! Shinigami no Sekai, 突入！死神の世界.

Ichigo and the others manage to make it through to the Soul Society...
name: Enter! The World of the Shinigami

description:
Japanese title: Shinigami o Nikumu Otoko, 死神を憎む男.

Ichigo and crew defeat the giant, but their entrance into the Seireitei is nowhere near smooth sailing...
name: The Man Who Hates Shinigami

description:
Japanese title: Rukia Shokei, Jūyokka Mae, ルキア処刑、14日前.

Ichigo and crew defeat the giant, but their entrance into the Seireitei is nowhere near smooth sailing...
name: 14 Days Before Rukia's Execution

description:
Japanese title: Kesshū! Gotei Jūsantai, 結集！護廷13隊.

Kukaku Shiba's plan is to catapult Ichigo and the others over the walls of the Seireitei with her very own creation, the Flower Crane Cannon.
name: Assemble! The 13 Divisions

description:
Japanese title: Kyodai Hōdan de Chūō Toppa? 巨大砲弾で中央突破？.

Ichigo, Chad, Uryu and Orihime concentrate on controlling their spirit energy for their flight into the Seireitei.
name: Penetrate The Center With An Enormous Bombshell?
